Package neupaths.api

Class CellFactory

java.lang.Object
neupaths.api.CellFactory
public class CellFactory extends Object
Creates cells according to cell definition files.

A cell definition file contains an XML schema for one of the NeuPaths cell types: BridgeCell, EventCell, ExtractorCell, InjectorCell, LogicCell or RouterCell. The createCell(java.lang.String) method instantiates a NeuPaths cell according to the definition, returning a reference to the specific NeuPaths cell type. For example, a cell definition file that specifies a Logic cell would be used as follows:

    LogicCell myCell = CellFactory.createCell(myCellDefinition);

If the cell type is unknown at runtime, a less specific instantiation would be:

    Cell myCell = CellFactory.createCell(myCellDefinition);

Bridge Cells

A BridgeCell is specified as follows: 

     <bridge_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapses>
         <synapse></synapse>
         ...
     </synapses>
     <subscriptions>
         <subscription>
             <cell_name></cell_name>
             <transmitter_name></transmitter_name>
             <domain></domain>
         </subscription>
         ...
     </subscriptions>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </bridge_cell>

Note: Subscriptions are optional. When no subscriptions are provided, the cell operates as a RouterCell.

Event Cells

An EventCell is specified as follows: 

     <event_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapse></synapse>
     <output_file></output_file>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </event_cell>

Extractor Cells

An ExtractorCell is specified as follows: 

     <extractor_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapses>
         <synapse></synapse>
         ...
     </synapses>
     <subscription>
         <cell_name></cell_name>
         <transmitter_name></transmitter_name>
         <domain></domain>
         <transaction_filter>enabled|disabled</transaction_filter>
     </subscription>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </extractor_cell>

Injector Cells

An InjectorCell is specified as follows: 

     <injector_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapses>
         <synapse></synapse>
         ...
     </synapses>
     <transmitter>
         <name></name>
         <stimulus_class></stimulus_class>
         <trace>enabled|disabled</trace>
     </transmitter>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </injector_cell>

Logic Cells

A LogicCell is specified as follows: 

     <logic_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapses>
         <synapse></synapse>
         ...
     </synapses>
     <activators>
         <activator>
             <class></class>
             <properties>
                 <property>
                     <name></name>
                     <value></value>
                 </property>
                 ...
             </properties>
             <transaction_history_window_ms></transaction_history_window_ms>
         </activator>
         ...
     </activators>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </logic_cell>

Note: Activator properties are optional.

Router Cells

A RouterCell is specified as follows: 

     <router_cell>
     <name></name>
     <synapses>
         <synapse></synapse>
         ...
     </synapses>
     <logging_enabled>true|false</logging_enabled>
     <trace_logging_enabled>true|false</trace_logging_enabled>
     <debug_logging_enabled>true|false</debug_logging_enabled>
     <runtime_logging_enabled>true|false</runtime_logging_enabled>
     <propagate_global_subscriptions>true|false</propagate_global_subscriptions>
     <subscription_refresh_interval_ms></subscription_refresh_interval_ms>
     <duplicate_detection_interval_ms></duplicate_detection_interval_ms>
     <subscription_trace_interval_ms></subscription_trace_interval_ms>
     <crypto_key_file></crypto_key_file>
 </router_cell>
